# SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
#
# An authenticating reverse proxy in front of the runner, using Caddy.
#
# Hearth keeps the runner alive but does not put it on the network. If you want
# to reach the runner's API from elsewhere, do not set the runner's host to
# 0.0.0.0 and expose it raw. Keep the runner on 127.0.0.1 and put an
# authenticating proxy in front of it. Proxying inference traffic is a job for a
# battle tested proxy, not something Hearth should reimplement; this is the
# recommended pattern.
#
# Install Caddy (brew install caddy), edit the address and token below, and run:
#   caddy run --config deploy/Caddyfile.example
#
# This example gates every request on a bearer token and forwards the rest to the
# local runner. Bind the site address to your Tailscale address (or use Caddy's
# automatic HTTPS with a real hostname) so it is not open to the whole internet.

# Replace with your Tailscale address or hostname and port.
100.64.0.2:8443 {
	@authorized header Authorization "Bearer CHANGE-ME-to-a-long-random-token"

	handle @authorized {
		# The runner's local address (Ollama default shown).
		reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:11434
	}

	# Anything without the right token gets nothing useful.
	respond "Unauthorized" 401
}
